author: Messenger Post sports@messengerpostmedia.com
title: High schools: Hawkins leads Palmyra-Macedon football past Wayne
text: Posted Oct. 16, 2015 at 10:45 PM Canandaigua, N.Y. It was another big night for Brandon Hawkins. But it was even bigger for the Wayne County Children’s Cancer Fund. The Palmyra-Macedon junior running back rushed for 333 yards and scored three touchdowns to lead the Red Raiders to a 42-30 win over Wayne on Friday night. Senior Andrew Kujawski added 132 yards for the Red Raiders (2-5), who rushed for 476 yards as a team in ending their five-game losing streak in the regular-season finale. Sophomore quarterback Braeden Zenelovic completed 15 of 24 passes for 230 yards and three TDs for Wayne (0-7). The teams combined to raise $3,000 for the Wayne County Children’s Cancer Fund. Mynderse 22, Marcus Whitman 12 Dylan Howell’s 39-yard touchdown run in the third quarter gave Marcus Whitman a 12-6 lead, but Mynderse answered with 16 unanswered points. Tyler Cummings, who finished with 37 rushing yards, scored Whitman’s first TD, on a 4-yard run. Howell, a freshman, led the Wildcats (0-7) with 137 yards on 15 carries and senior Gavin McCumiskey caught five passes for 54 yards. Girls soccer Bloomfield 3, Honeoye 2 Jill Marianacci scored two goals for Bloomfield and Lily Nelson also scored for the Bombers (12-4). Sarah Barker made two saves for Bloomfield and Braelin Scott assisted on a goal. Sara Jane Stevens and Ashton Allison scored for Honeoye (5-11). Naples 5, Dundee 0 Emma Lincoln and Skyler Matthews each scored two goals for the Big Green (13-2-1), and Mika Hobart also scored. Naples scored all five goals in the first half. Katie Lincoln had two assists and Mackenzie Northrup had one. Boys volleyball Max Colcord had 11 kills and Max Tucker had eight kills for Canandaigua (2-10). For Victor (8-5), Paul Kopp had 14 kills and Cam Clark had 44 assists. Girls volleyball Canandaigua 25-16-25-24, Rush-Henrietta 20-25-17-16 Outside hitter Rachel Simmons had nine kills and three aces, while Dale Sandle had 11 digs for Canandaigua (5-8). Cami Smeatin added five kills and three blocks for the Braves. Bloomfield 25-25-25, Dundee 12-17-22 Sierra Leitten had 9 aces, 6 kills and 9 assists, while Bella Iacavangelo had seven aces and 10 assists for Bloomfield (6-7). For Dundee, Jeanette Jayne had 2 kills, 2 assists and 2 digs. Palmyra-Macedon 25-25-25, Gananda 21-23-21 Michaela Morrison had 16 assists and Lindsay Howell had 10 kills for Pal-Mac. Riley Beard added 12 digs for the Red Raiders. Thursday Boys soccer Canandaigua 2, Brighton 0 Canandaigua (11-4-1) wrapped up its regular season with its seventh shutout of the season. Junior Jonathon Brown scored both goals for the Braves, one in each half. Canandaigua awaits its Section V Class A seeding and will play its first tournament game on Friday. Girls swimming Penfield 109, Canandaigua 75 Serica Hallstead won the diving event with a score of 272 and Sabrina Turek won the 200-yard individual medley with a time of 2:18.03 for Canandaigua (3-5). Other winners for the Braves include Kaitlyn Ringhoff 100 backstroke (1:04.70) and the 400 freestyle relay team of Sarah Alling, Meghan Bates, Melina Brunelli and Ringhoff (4:04). Palmyra-Macedon 101, Newark 80 Rachel Mayou won the 200 IM (2:36.68) and the 100 free (:59.67) for Pal-Mac and Olivia Viens won the 500 free in :28.49. Also for Pal-Mac, Alanna Viscosi won the 100 butterfly (1:12.42), Audrey Quinn won the 500 free (5:59.09), Delaney Leeson won the 100 back (1:11.38) and Julia Lioudis won the 100 breaststroke (1:21.41). By Messenger Post
